cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for medical image analysis, specifically for melanoma classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the selection of CNN architectures, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of transfer learning and ensembling also suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the evaluation of the models on the ISIC Challenge 2017 dataset involves the use of medical images, which could also place the paper under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
